      "details": "1. Define the AnalysisProfile data model (ID, Name, Instructions, SchemaDefinition, timestamps)\n2. Implement storage backend (SQLite database or JSON file-based storage)\n3. Create CRUD operations for profiles (Create, Read, Update, Delete)\n4. Add methods to save and load profiles\n5. Implement basic validation for profile data\n6. Create utility functions for profile management\n7. Add error handling for storage operations\n8. Ensure proper serialization/deserialization of JSON schema definitions",
      "testStrategy": "Test CRUD operations with sample profiles, verify data persistence across application restarts, validate schema storage and retrieval, and check error handling for invalid inputs.",
      "subtasks": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "title": "1. Define the AnalysisProfile data model (ID, Name, Instructions, SchemaDefinition, timestamps)",
          "description": "Create the core data model class for Analysis Profiles with all required attributes according to the PRD specifications.",
          "details": "1. Create an AnalysisProfile class with the following attributes:\n   - id: Unique identifier (UUID)\n   - name: String for profile name (required, must be unique)\n   - instructions: Text field for analysis instructions to guide the analysis process\n   - schema_definition: JSON structure defining the analysis schema with input/output fields\n   - created_at: Timestamp for creation date\n   - updated_at: Timestamp for last modification\n2. Implement appropriate getters and setters\n3. Add validation for required fields (name cannot be empty, schema must be valid JSON)\n4. Include proper type annotations for all fields\n5. Implement __str__ and __repr__ methods for debugging\n6. Add methods for schema validation against expected structure\n7. Ensure the model supports versioning for future compatibility\n\n<info added on 2025-05-04T02:36:45.763Z>\nHere's additional information to enhance the subtask:\n\n```python\n# Example implementation of the AnalysisProfile class\nimport uuid\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport json\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, Optional\n\nclass AnalysisProfile:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        instructions: str = \"\",\n        schema_definition: Dict[str, Any] = None,\n        id: Optional[uuid.UUID] = None,\n        created_at: Optional[datetime] = None,\n        updated_at: Optional[datetime] = None\n    ):\n        self.id = id or uuid.uuid4()\n        self.name = name\n        self.instructions = instructions\n        self.schema_definition = schema_definition or {}\n        self.created_at = created_at or datetime.utcnow()\n        self.updated_at = updated_at or self.created_at\n        \n        # Validate on initialization\n        if not self.is_valid():\n            raise ValueError(\"Invalid AnalysisProfile parameters\")\n    \n    def is_valid(self) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Validate the profile has required fields and proper structure\"\"\"\n        if not self.name or not isinstance(self.name, str):\n            return False\n            \n        # Validate schema structure - check for required components\n        try:\n            if self.schema_definition:\n                # Ensure schema has input and output sections\n                if not all(k in self.schema_definition for k in ['input', 'output']):\n                    return False\n        except Exception:\n            return False\n            \n        return True\n        \n    def update(self, **kwargs) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Update profile attributes and set updated_at timestamp\"\"\"\n        for key, value in kwargs.items():\n            if hasattr(self, key):\n                setattr(self, key, value)\n        self.updated_at = datetime.utcnow()\n    \n    def to_dict(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Convert profile to dictionary for serialization\"\"\"\n        return {\n            'id': str(self.id),\n            'name': self.name,\n            'instructions': self.instructions,\n            'schema_definition': self.schema_definition,\n            'created_at': self.created_at.isoformat(),\n            'updated_at': self.updated_at.isoformat()\n        }\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def from_dict(cls, data: Dict[str, Any]) -> 'AnalysisProfile':\n        \"\"\"Create profile from dictionary representation\"\"\"\n        return cls(\n            id=uuid.UUID(data['id']) if isinstance(data.get('id'), str) else data.get('id'),\n            name=data['name'],\n            instructions=data.get('instructions', ''),\n            schema_definition=data.get('schema_definition', {}),\n            created_at=datetime.fromisoformat(data['created_at']) if isinstance(data.get('created_at'), str) else data.get('created_at'),\n            updated_at=datetime.fromisoformat(data['updated_at']) if isinstance(data.get('updated_at'), str) else data.get('updated_at')\n        )\n```\n\nConsider implementing a schema validator method that checks the structure against a predefined JSON schema template. This could validate that input/output fields follow expected patterns and contain required properties like field names, types, and descriptions.\n</info added on 2025-05-04T02:36:45.763Z>",
