        {
          "id": 2,
          "title": "2. Implement storage backend (SQLite database or JSON file-based storage)",
          "description": "Create a persistent storage mechanism for Analysis Profiles that ensures data integrity and efficient access.",
          "details": "1. Evaluate and select the most appropriate storage solution:\n   - SQLite for structured data with transaction support\n   - JSON file storage for simplicity and portability\n2. For SQLite implementation:\n   - Design normalized database schema with profiles table\n   - Create indexes for frequent query patterns (id, name)\n   - Implement connection pooling for performance\n   - Add migration framework for schema evolution\n3. For JSON file storage:\n   - Define consistent file structure with metadata\n   - Implement atomic write operations to prevent corruption\n   - Add file locking mechanism for concurrent access\n   - Create automatic backup system before writes\n4. Implement storage factory pattern to abstract storage details\n5. Add configuration options for storage location\n6. Include performance monitoring for storage operations\n7. Implement storage integrity verification\n\n<info added on 2025-05-04T02:37:10.522Z>\nHere's additional information to enhance the subtask:\n\n```\n8. Error handling and recovery:\n   - Implement robust error handling for storage failures\n   - Create automatic recovery mechanisms for corrupted data\n   - Add logging for all storage operations with appropriate detail levels\n\n9. Data validation layer:\n   - Implement pre-storage validation to ensure data integrity\n   - Add schema versioning to support backward compatibility\n   - Create data sanitization routines to prevent injection attacks\n\n10. Performance optimization:\n    - Implement caching layer for frequently accessed profiles\n    - Add bulk operation support for batch processing\n    - Create query optimization for filtered retrievals\n    - Consider implementing read/write splitting for high-load scenarios\n\n11. For SQLite specifically:\n    - Use WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) journal mode for better concurrency\n    - Implement prepared statements for all queries to prevent SQL injection\n    - Add foreign key constraints if implementing related tables\n    - Configure appropriate busy timeout and retry logic\n\n12. Testing infrastructure:\n    - Create mock storage implementation for unit testing\n    - Implement storage stress tests for concurrent access\n    - Add data corruption tests to verify recovery mechanisms\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-04T02:37:10.522Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-04T02:57:55.376Z>\n```\n13. SQLite Implementation Details:\n    - Database file location: Store at `~/.config/analysis_profiles/profiles.db` with configurable override\n    - Schema creation SQL:\n      ```sql\n      CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS profiles (\n          id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n          name TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n          instructions TEXT,\n          schema_definition TEXT NOT NULL,\n          created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n          updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n      );\n      CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_profiles_name ON profiles(name);\n      CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_profiles_updated_at ON profiles(updated_at);\n      ```\n    - Use SQLite's JSON1 extension for efficient schema_definition storage and querying\n    - Implement connection timeout handling with exponential backoff (max 5 retries)\n\n14. Storage Interface Implementation:\n    - Define `StorageInterface` with methods:\n      ```python\n      class StorageInterface(ABC):\n          @abstractmethod\n          def get_profile(self, id_or_name: str) -> Optional[Profile]: pass\n          \n          @abstractmethod\n          def save_profile(self, profile: Profile) -> bool: pass\n          \n          @abstractmethod\n          def list_profiles(self, filter_criteria: Optional[Dict] = None) -> List[Profile]: pass\n          \n          @abstractmethod\n          def delete_profile(self, id_or_name: str) -> bool: pass\n      ```\n    - Implement transaction management in SQLiteStorage with context managers\n    - Add profile versioning support with optimistic locking to prevent concurrent modification conflicts\n\n15. Migration Strategy:\n    - Use Alembic for schema migrations to support future database changes\n    - Implement data migration utilities for converting between storage backends\n    - Add database integrity check on application startup\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-04T02:57:55.376Z>",
