          "parentTaskId": 2
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "title": "6. Create utility functions for profile management",
          "description": "Develop a comprehensive set of helper functions to simplify common profile operations and enhance usability.",
          "details": "1. Create profile management utilities:\n   - clone_profile(): Create a copy with new ID and optional name changes\n   - create_template_profile(): Generate starter profiles for common use cases\n   - diff_profiles(): Compare two profiles and identify differences\n   - merge_profiles(): Combine elements from multiple profiles\n2. Implement search capabilities:\n   - search_profiles_by_text(): Full-text search across all text fields\n   - find_profiles_by_schema_element(): Find profiles containing specific schema elements\n3. Add schema manipulation utilities:\n   - extract_schema_section(): Get specific parts of a schema\n   - validate_schema_compatibility(): Check if schemas are compatible\n   - upgrade_schema_version(): Convert between schema versions\n4. Implement profile categorization and tagging\n5. Add profile usage statistics tracking\n6. Create profile dependency analysis tools\n7. Implement profile documentation generation\n8. Add profile visualization helpers\n\n<info added on 2025-05-04T02:44:42.133Z>\nHere's additional implementation information for the utility functions:\n\n```python\n# Implementation details for profile management utilities\n\ndef clone_profile(source_id: str, new_name: str = None, modifications: dict = None) -> AnalysisProfile:\n    \"\"\"\n    Creates a copy of an existing profile with optional modifications.\n    \n    Args:\n        source_id: ID of the profile to clone\n        new_name: Optional new name (defaults to \"Copy of [original name]\")\n        modifications: Dictionary of attributes to modify in the new profile\n        \n    Returns:\n        The newly created profile\n    \"\"\"\n    # Implementation example with deep copying to avoid reference issues\n    import copy\n    source = load_profile(source_id)\n    if not source:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Source profile with ID {source_id} not found\")\n        \n    # Deep copy to avoid reference issues with nested objects\n    new_profile = copy.deepcopy(source)\n    new_profile.id = str(uuid.uuid4())\n    new_profile.name = new_name or f\"Copy of {source.name}\"\n    new_profile.created_at = datetime.now()\n    new_profile.updated_at = datetime.now()\n    \n    # Apply any modifications\n    if modifications:\n        for key, value in modifications.items():\n            if hasattr(new_profile, key):\n                setattr(new_profile, key, value)\n    \n    # Save and return\n    return save_profile(new_profile)\n\ndef create_template_profile(template_type: str, name: str = None) -> AnalysisProfile:\n    \"\"\"\n    Creates a pre-configured profile based on common use cases.\n    \n    Template types:\n    - \"basic\": Minimal schema with core fields\n    - \"detailed\": Comprehensive schema with all standard fields\n    - \"security\": Schema focused on security analysis\n    - \"performance\": Schema focused on performance metrics\n    \"\"\"\n    templates = {\n        \"basic\": {\n            \"schema_definition\": {\n                \"version\": \"1.0\",\n                \"fields\": [\n                    {\"name\": \"summary\", \"type\": \"text\", \"required\": True},\n                    {\"name\": \"key_findings\", \"type\": \"list\", \"required\": True},\n                ]\n            },\n            \"instructions\": \"Provide a basic analysis with summary and key findings.\"\n        },\n        \"detailed\": {\n            # More comprehensive schema definition\n        },\n        # Additional templates...\n    }\n    \n    if template_type not in templates:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown template type: {template_type}. Available types: {', '.join(templates.keys())}\")\n    \n    template = templates[template_type]\n    profile = AnalysisProfile(\n        id=str(uuid.uuid4()),\n        name=name or f\"{template_type.capitalize()} Analysis Template\",\n        schema_definition=template[\"schema_definition\"],\n        instructions=template[\"instructions\"],\n        created_at=datetime.now(),\n        updated_at=datetime.now()\n    )\n    \n    return save_profile(profile)\n\ndef diff_profiles(profile_id1: str, profile_id2: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Compares two profiles and returns their differences.\n    \n    Returns a dictionary with keys for each differing attribute,\n    containing both values in a tuple (profile1_value, profile2_value)\n    \"\"\"\n    import deepdiff\n    \n    profile1 = load_profile(profile_id1)\n    profile2 = load_profile(profile_id2)\n    \n    # Convert to dictionaries, excluding metadata fields\n    dict1 = {k: v for k, v in profile1.to_dict().items() \n             if k not in ['id', 'created_at', 'updated_at']}\n    dict2 = {k: v for k, v in profile2.to_dict().items() \n             if k not in ['id', 'created_at', 'updated_at']}\n    \n    # Use DeepDiff for nested dictionary comparison\n    differences = deepdiff.DeepDiff(dict1, dict2, ignore_order=True)\n    \n    # Format the results for easier consumption\n    formatted_diff = {\n        \"schema_differences\": [],\n        \"instruction_differences\": False,\n        \"name_different\": profile1.name != profile2.name,\n        \"summary\": f\"Found {len(differences)} differences between profiles\"\n    }\n    \n    # Process schema differences specifically\n    if 'schema_definition' in differences:\n        # Extract specific schema field differences\n        # Implementation depends on schema structure\n        pass\n        \n    return formatted_diff\n```\n\nFor the search capabilities:\n\n```python\ndef search_profiles_by_text(query: str, search_fields: List[str] = None) -> List[AnalysisProfile]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Performs full-text search across profile text fields.\n    \n    Args:\n        query: Text to search for\n        search_fields: List of fields to search (defaults to ['name', 'instructions'])\n        \n    Returns:\n        List of matching profiles\n    \"\"\"\n    if search_fields is None:\n        search_fields = ['name', 'instructions']\n    \n    # For SQLite implementation using FTS5:\n    conn = get_database_connection()\n    \n    # Build query dynamically based on search_fields\n    field_conditions = \" OR \".join([f\"{field} LIKE ?\" for field in search_fields])\n    params = [f\"%{query}%\" for _ in search_fields]\n    \n    sql = f\"\"\"\n    SELECT * FROM analysis_profiles \n    WHERE {field_conditions}\n    ORDER BY name\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    cursor = conn.execute(sql, params)\n    results = [AnalysisProfile.from_dict(dict(row)) for row in cursor.fetchall()]\n    conn.close()\n    \n    return results\n\ndef validate_schema_compatibility(schema1: dict, schema2: dict) -> Tuple[bool, List[str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Checks if two schemas are compatible for data exchange or merging.\n    \n    Returns:\n        Tuple containing (is_compatible, list_of_incompatibilities)\n    \"\"\"\n    incompatibilities = []\n    \n    # Check schema versions\n    if schema1.get(\"version\") != schema2.get(\"version\"):\n        incompatibilities.append(f\"Version mismatch: {schema1.get('version')} vs {schema2.get('version')}\")\n    \n    # Check required fields\n    schema1_required = {f[\"name\"] for f in schema1.get(\"fields\", []) if f.get(\"required\")}\n    schema2_required = {f[\"name\"] for f in schema2.get(\"fields\", []) if f.get(\"required\")}\n    \n    # Check if schema2 has all required fields from schema1\n    missing_required = schema1_required - {f[\"name\"] for f in schema2.get(\"fields\", [])}\n    if missing_required:\n        incompatibilities.append(f\"Missing required fields: {', '.join(missing_required)}\")\n    \n    # Check field type compatibility\n    schema1_fields = {f[\"name\"]: f[\"type\"] for f in schema1.get(\"fields\", [])}\n    schema2_fields = {f[\"name\"]: f[\"type\"] for f in schema2.get(\"fields\", [])}\n    \n    for name, type1 in schema1_fields.items():\n        if name in schema2_fields and schema2_fields[name] != type1:\n            incompatibilities.append(f\"Field type mismatch for '{name}': {type1} vs {schema2_fields[name]}\")\n    \n    return (len(incompatibilities) == 0, incompatibilities)\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-04T02:44:42.133Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-04T02:45:27.218Z>\nHere's additional implementation information for profile import/export functionality:\n\n```python\ndef export_profile(profile_id: str, include_metadata: bool = True) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Exports a profile to a JSON string representation.\n    \n    Args:\n        profile_id: ID of the profile to export\n        include_metadata: Whether to include creation/update timestamps\n        \n    Returns:\n        JSON string representation of the profile\n    \"\"\"\n    profile = load_profile(profile_id)\n    if not profile:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Profile with ID {profile_id} not found\")\n    \n    # Convert to dictionary\n    profile_dict = profile.to_dict()\n    \n    # Optionally remove metadata\n    if not include_metadata:\n        for field in ['created_at', 'updated_at']:\n            if field in profile_dict:\n                del profile_dict[field]\n    \n    # Convert datetime objects to ISO format strings for JSON serialization\n    for key, value in profile_dict.items():\n        if isinstance(value, datetime):\n            profile_dict[key] = value.isoformat()\n    \n    return json.dumps(profile_dict, indent=2)\n\ndef import_profile(profile_json_string: str, \n                   generate_new_id: bool = True,\n                   handle_name_conflicts: str = 'rename') -> AnalysisProfile:\n    \"\"\"\n    Imports a profile from a JSON string representation.\n    \n    Args:\n        profile_json_string: JSON string representation of the profile\n        generate_new_id: Whether to generate a new ID (True) or use the one in the JSON (False)\n        handle_name_conflicts: How to handle name conflicts:\n            - 'rename': Automatically rename by adding a suffix\n            - 'error': Raise an error\n            - 'overwrite': Overwrite existing profile with same name\n            \n    Returns:\n        The imported profile\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        profile_dict = json.loads(profile_json_string)\n    except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Invalid JSON format: {str(e)}\")\n    \n    # Validate required fields\n    required_fields = ['name', 'schema_definition', 'instructions']\n    for field in required_fields:\n        if field not in profile_dict:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Missing required field: {field}\")\n    \n    # Validate schema structure\n    schema_validator = SchemaValidator()\n    validation_result = schema_validator.validate_schema(profile_dict['schema_definition'])\n    if not validation_result.is_valid:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Invalid schema: {validation_result.errors}\")\n    \n    # Handle ID generation\n    if generate_new_id or 'id' not in profile_dict:\n        profile_dict['id'] = str(uuid.uuid4())\n    \n    # Handle name conflicts\n    existing_profiles = find_profiles_by_name(profile_dict['name'])\n    if existing_profiles and handle_name_conflicts != 'overwrite':\n        if handle_name_conflicts == 'error':\n            raise ValueError(f\"A profile with name '{profile_dict['name']}' already exists\")\n        elif handle_name_conflicts == 'rename':\n            # Find a unique name by adding a suffix\n            base_name = profile_dict['name']\n            counter = 1\n            while find_profiles_by_name(f\"{base_name} ({counter})\"):\n                counter += 1\n            profile_dict['name'] = f\"{base_name} ({counter})\"\n    \n    # Set timestamps\n    now = datetime.now()\n    profile_dict['created_at'] = now\n    profile_dict['updated_at'] = now\n    \n    # Convert to AnalysisProfile object\n    profile = AnalysisProfile.from_dict(profile_dict)\n    \n    # Save and return\n    return save_profile(profile)\n\ndef find_profiles_by_name(name: str) -> List[AnalysisProfile]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds profiles by exact name match.\n    \n    Args:\n        name: Name to search for\n        \n    Returns:\n        List of matching profiles (usually 0 or 1)\n    \"\"\"\n    conn = get_database_connection()\n    cursor = conn.execute(\n        \"SELECT * FROM analysis_profiles WHERE name = ?\", \n        (name,)\n    )\n    results = [AnalysisProfile.from_dict(dict(row)) for row in cursor.fetchall()]\n    conn.close()\n    return results\n\ndef merge_profiles(profile_ids: List[str], \n                   new_name: str,\n                   merge_strategy: str = 'union') -> AnalysisProfile:\n    \"\"\"\n    Combines elements from multiple profiles into a new profile.\n    \n    Args:\n        profile_ids: List of profile IDs to merge\n        new_name: Name for the merged profile\n        merge_strategy: How to handle conflicts:\n            - 'union': Include all fields from all profiles\n            - 'intersection': Include only fields present in all profiles\n            - 'primary': Use first profile as base, add missing fields from others\n            \n    Returns:\n        The newly created merged profile\n    \"\"\"\n    if len(profile_ids) < 2:\n        raise ValueError(\"At least two profiles are required for merging\")\n    \n    profiles = [load_profile(pid) for pid in profile_ids]\n    if None in profiles:\n        missing = [pid for pid, p in zip(profile_ids, profiles) if p is None]\n        raise ValueError(f\"Profiles not found: {', '.join(missing)}\")\n    \n    # Create new profile with basic metadata\n    merged_profile = AnalysisProfile(\n        id=str(uuid.uuid4()),\n        name=new_name,\n        created_at=datetime.now(),\n        updated_at=datetime.now()\n    )\n    \n    # Merge instructions (concatenate with headers)\n    merged_profile.instructions = \"\\n\\n\".join([\n        f\"--- From profile '{p.name}' ---\\n{p.instructions}\" \n        for p in profiles\n    ])\n    \n    # Merge schema definitions based on strategy\n    if merge_strategy == 'primary':\n        merged_profile.schema_definition = copy.deepcopy(profiles[0].schema_definition)\n    else:\n        # Implementation for union/intersection strategies\n        # This would require more complex schema merging logic\n        pass\n    \n    return save_profile(merged_profile)\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-04T02:45:27.218Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-04T04:20:50.753Z>\nHere's additional implementation information for the missing items:\n\n```python\ndef merge_profiles_with_strategy(profile_ids: List[str], \n                   new_name: str,\n                   merge_strategy: str = 'union') -> AnalysisProfile:\n    \"\"\"\n    Enhanced implementation of merge_profiles with complete strategy support.\n    \"\"\"\n    # ... [existing code from previous implementation] ...\n    \n    # Merge schema definitions based on strategy\n    if merge_strategy == 'primary':\n        merged_profile.schema_definition = copy.deepcopy(profiles[0].schema_definition)\n    elif merge_strategy == 'union':\n        # Combine all fields from all profiles, removing duplicates\n        all_fields = []\n        field_names = set()\n        \n        for profile in profiles:\n            for field in profile.schema_definition.get('fields', []):\n                if field['name'] not in field_names:\n                    all_fields.append(copy.deepcopy(field))\n                    field_names.add(field['name'])\n                    \n        merged_profile.schema_definition = {\n            \"version\": max(p.schema_definition.get('version', '1.0') for p in profiles),\n            \"fields\": all_fields\n        }\n    elif merge_strategy == 'intersection':\n        # Only include fields that exist in all profiles\n        # First, collect all field definitions by name\n        field_definitions = {}\n        field_counts = {}\n        \n        for profile in profiles:\n            for field in profile.schema_definition.get('fields', []):\n                name = field['name']\n                if name not in field_definitions:\n                    field_definitions[name] = field\n                    field_counts[name] = 1\n                else:\n                    field_counts[name] += 1\n        \n        # Only keep fields that appear in all profiles\n        common_fields = [\n            copy.deepcopy(field_definitions[name]) \n            for name, count in field_counts.items() \n            if count == len(profiles)\n        ]\n        \n        merged_profile.schema_definition = {\n            \"version\": min(p.schema_definition.get('version', '1.0') for p in profiles),\n            \"fields\": common_fields\n        }\n    \n    return save_profile(merged_profile)\n\ndef upgrade_schema_version(profile_id: str, target_version: str) -> AnalysisProfile:\n    \"\"\"\n    Upgrades a profile's schema to a newer version.\n    \n    Args:\n        profile_id: ID of the profile to upgrade\n        target_version: Version to upgrade to (e.g., \"2.0\")\n        \n    Returns:\n        The upgraded profile\n    \"\"\"\n    profile = load_profile(profile_id)\n    if not profile:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Profile with ID {profile_id} not found\")\n    \n    current_version = profile.schema_definition.get(\"version\", \"1.0\")\n    \n    # Skip if already at target version\n    if current_version == target_version:\n        return profile\n    \n    # Define version upgrade paths\n    upgrade_paths = {\n        \"1.0-to-2.0\": _upgrade_1_0_to_2_0,\n        \"2.0-to-3.0\": _upgrade_2_0_to_3_0,\n        # Add more upgrade paths as needed\n    }\n    \n    # Determine upgrade path\n    path_key = f\"{current_version}-to-{target_version}\"\n    if path_key not in upgrade_paths:\n        # Try to find a multi-step path\n        if current_version == \"1.0\" and target_version == \"3.0\":\n            # Two-step upgrade: 1.0 -> 2.0 -> 3.0\n            profile = _upgrade_1_0_to_2_0(profile)\n            return _upgrade_2_0_to_3_0(profile)\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"No upgrade path from {current_version} to {target_version}\")\n    \n    # Execute the upgrade\n    upgraded_profile = upgrade_paths[path_key](profile)\n    upgraded_profile.updated_at = datetime.now()\n    \n    return save_profile(upgraded_profile)\n\ndef _upgrade_1_0_to_2_0(profile: AnalysisProfile) -> AnalysisProfile:\n    \"\"\"\n    Upgrades a profile from schema v1.0 to v2.0.\n    \n    Changes:\n    - Adds 'description' field to each schema field\n    - Converts 'list' type to 'array' with 'items' property\n    - Adds 'metadata' section to schema\n    \"\"\"\n    schema = copy.deepcopy(profile.schema_definition)\n    schema[\"version\"] = \"2.0\"\n    \n    # Add metadata section if not present\n    if \"metadata\" not in schema:\n        schema[\"metadata\"] = {\n            \"created_from\": \"v1.0 upgrade\",\n            \"upgrade_date\": datetime.now().isoformat()\n        }\n    \n    # Update fields\n    for field in schema.get(\"fields\", []):\n        # Add description if missing\n        if \"description\" not in field:\n            field[\"description\"] = f\"Auto-generated description for {field['name']}\"\n        \n        # Convert list type to array\n        if field.get(\"type\") == \"list\":\n            field[\"type\"] = \"array\"\n            if \"items\" not in field:\n                field[\"items\"] = {\"type\": \"string\"}\n    \n    profile.schema_definition = schema\n    return profile\n\ndef _upgrade_2_0_to_3_0(profile: AnalysisProfile) -> AnalysisProfile:\n    \"\"\"\n    Upgrades a profile from schema v2.0 to v3.0.\n    \n    Changes:\n    - Adds 'validation' property to fields\n    - Restructures schema to use 'properties' instead of 'fields'\n    - Adds 'schema_type' field\n    \"\"\"\n    old_schema = copy.deepcopy(profile.schema_definition)\n    \n    # Create new schema structure\n    new_schema = {\n        \"version\": \"3.0\",\n        \"schema_type\": \"analysis_profile\",\n        \"properties\": {},\n        \"required\": [],\n        \"metadata\": old_schema.get(\"metadata\", {})\n    }\n    \n    # Update metadata\n    new_schema[\"metadata\"][\"upgraded_from\"] = \"2.0\"\n    new_schema[\"metadata\"][\"upgrade_date\"] = datetime.now().isoformat()\n    \n    # Convert fields to properties\n    for field in old_schema.get(\"fields\", []):\n        field_name = field[\"name\"]\n        property_def = {\n            \"type\": field[\"type\"],\n            \"description\": field.get(\"description\", \"\")\n        }\n        \n        # Add validation rules\n        if field[\"type\"] == \"string\" or field[\"type\"] == \"text\":\n            property_def[\"validation\"] = {\n                \"min_length\": 0,\n                \"max_length\": 1000\n            }\n        elif field[\"type\"] == \"array\":\n            property_def[\"items\"] = field.get(\"items\", {\"type\": \"string\"})\n            property_def[\"validation\"] = {\n                \"min_items\": 0,\n                \"max_items\": 100\n            }\n        \n        new_schema[\"properties\"][field_name] = property_def\n        \n        # Add to required list if needed\n        if field.get(\"required\", False):\n            new_schema[\"required\"].append(field_name)\n    \n    profile.schema_definition = new_schema\n    return profile\n\n# Implementation for profile categorization and tagging\ndef add_tags_to_profile(profile_id: str, tags: List[str]) -> AnalysisProfile:\n    \"\"\"\n    Adds tags to a profile for categorization and filtering.\n    \n    Args:\n        profile_id: ID of the profile to tag\n        tags: List of tag strings to add\n        \n    Returns:\n        The updated profile\n    \"\"\"\n    profile = load_profile(profile_id)\n    if not profile:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Profile with ID {profile_id} not found\")\n    \n    # Initialize tags if not present\n    if not hasattr(profile, 'tags') or profile.tags is None:\n        profile.tags = []\n    \n    # Add new tags (avoid duplicates)\n    for tag in tags:\n        if tag not in profile.tags:\n            profile.tags.append(tag)\n    \n    profile.updated_at = datetime.now()\n    return save_profile(profile)\n\ndef get_profiles_by_tag(tag: str) -> List[AnalysisProfile]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Retrieves all profiles with a specific tag.\n    \n    Args:\n        tag: Tag to search for\n        \n    Returns:\n        List of profiles with the specified tag\n    \"\"\"\n    conn = get_database_connection()\n    cursor = conn.execute(\n        \"SELECT * FROM analysis_profiles WHERE tags LIKE ?\", \n        (f\"%{tag}%\",)  # Simple implementation; a proper one would use JSON querying\n    )\n    results = [AnalysisProfile.from_dict(dict(row)) for row in cursor.fetchall()]\n    conn.close()\n    \n    # Filter results to ensure exact tag match\n    return [p for p in results if hasattr(p, 'tags') and tag in p.tags]\n\n# Profile usage statistics tracking\ndef record_profile_usage(profile_id: str, usage_type: str = 'view') -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Records a usage event for a profile.\n    \n    Args:\n        profile_id: ID of the profile used\n        usage_type: Type of usage ('view', 'edit', 'export', 'analysis')\n    \"\"\"\n    conn = get_database_connection()\n    conn.execute(\n        \"INSERT INTO profile_usage_stats (profile_id, usage_type, timestamp) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\",\n        (profile_id, usage_type, datetime.now())\n    )\n    conn.commit()\n    conn.close()\n\ndef get_profile_usage_stats(profile_id: str = None, days: int = 30) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Retrieves usage statistics for profiles.\n    \n    Args:\n        profile_id: Optional ID to filter for a specific profile\n        days: Number of days to look back\n        \n    Returns:\n        Dictionary with usage statistics\n    \"\"\"\n    conn = get_database_connection()\n    \n    # Calculate the date threshold\n    threshold_date = (datetime.now() - timedelta(days=days)).strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\n    \n    if profile_id:\n        # Stats for a specific profile\n        cursor = conn.execute(\n            \"\"\"\n            SELECT usage_type, COUNT(*) as count \n            FROM profile_usage_stats \n            WHERE profile_id = ? AND timestamp >= ?\n            GROUP BY usage_type\n            \"\"\",\n            (profile_id, threshold_date)\n        )\n        \n        stats = {row[0]: row[1] for row in cursor.fetchall()}\n        \n        # Get most active days\n        cursor = conn.execute(\n            \"\"\"\n            SELECT strftime('%Y-%m-%d', timestamp) as day, COUNT(*) as count\n            FROM profile_usage_stats\n            WHERE profile_id = ? AND timestamp >= ?\n            GROUP BY day\n            ORDER BY count DESC\n            LIMIT 5\n            \"\"\",\n            (profile_id, threshold_date)\n        )\n        \n        stats['most_active_days'] = {row[0]: row[1] for row in cursor.fetchall()}\n    else:\n        # Overall stats for all profiles\n        cursor = conn.execute(\n            \"\"\"\n            SELECT profile_id, COUNT(*) as count\n            FROM profile_usage_stats\n            WHERE timestamp >= ?\n            GROUP BY profile_id\n            ORDER BY count DESC\n            LIMIT 10\n            \"\"\",\n            (threshold_date,)\n        )\n        \n        stats = {'most_used_profiles': {}}\n        for row in cursor.fetchall():\n            profile = load_profile(row[0])\n            if profile:\n                stats['most_used_profiles'][profile.name] = row[1]\n    \n    conn.close()\n    return stats\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-04T04:20:50.753Z>",
