      "details": "1. Create main application window/layout\n2. Implement large text area for transcript input\n3. Build UI for profile management (list, create, edit, delete)\n4. Add form elements for profile name and instructions\n5. Implement profile selection mechanism (initially single selection)\n6. Create a 'Process' button to trigger analysis\n7. Add basic status indicators for processing state\n8. Implement error message display",
      "testStrategy": "Perform manual UI testing for layout and functionality, verify form validation, test profile creation and selection, and ensure proper error message display.",
      "subtasks": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "title": "Create main application window and transcript input area",
          "description": "Implement the main application layout and the transcript input component",
          "dependencies": [],
          "details": "Implementation steps:\n1. Create a responsive main application container with appropriate padding and margins\n2. Implement a header section with application title and basic navigation\n3. Design and implement a large text area component for transcript input with:\n   - Placeholder text guiding users on what to input\n   - Character count indicator\n   - Clear button functionality\n   - Auto-save capability for draft transcripts\n4. Add appropriate styling and ensure the text area is responsive\n5. Implement basic keyboard shortcuts (Ctrl+A to select all, etc.)\n\nTesting approach:\n- Verify text area properly accepts, displays and maintains large text inputs\n- Test responsiveness across different screen sizes\n- Validate that auto-save functionality works correctly\n- Ensure keyboard shortcuts function as expected\n\n<info added on 2025-05-05T01:07:26.870Z>\n# Implementation with customtkinter\n\n## Setup and Structure\n1. Install customtkinter: `pip install customtkinter`\n2. Create a modular structure:\n   - `src/main_app.py` - Main application class\n   - `src/components/transcript_input.py` - Encapsulated transcript component\n\n## Code Implementation\n\n```python\n# src/main_app.py\nimport customtkinter as ctk\nfrom components.transcript_input import TranscriptInput\n\nclass GrokApp(ctk.CTk):\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__()\n        \n        # Configure window\n        self.title(\"Transcript Analyzer\")\n        self.geometry(\"900x700\")\n        ctk.set_appearance_mode(\"System\")  # Use system theme\n        ctk.set_default_color_theme(\"blue\")\n        \n        # Configure grid layout (4x4)\n        self.grid_columnconfigure(0, weight=1)\n        self.grid_rowconfigure(1, weight=1)\n        \n        # Header\n        self.header = ctk.CTkLabel(self, text=\"Transcript Analyzer\", font=ctk.CTkFont(size=20, weight=\"bold\"))\n        self.header.grid(row=0, column=0, padx=20, pady=(20, 10), sticky=\"nw\")\n        \n        # Transcript input area\n        self.transcript_input = TranscriptInput(self)\n        self.transcript_input.grid(row=1, column=0, padx=20, pady=(0, 20), sticky=\"nsew\")\n\n# src/components/transcript_input.py\nimport customtkinter as ctk\nimport time\n\nclass TranscriptInput(ctk.CTkFrame):\n    def __init__(self, master):\n        super().__init__(master)\n        \n        # Configure grid layout\n        self.grid_columnconfigure(0, weight=1)\n        self.grid_rowconfigure(0, weight=1)\n        self.grid_rowconfigure(1, weight=0)\n        \n        # Text area\n        self.textbox = ctk.CTkTextbox(self, wrap=\"word\", font=ctk.CTkFont(size=14))\n        self.textbox.grid(row=0, column=0, padx=10, pady=(10, 5), sticky=\"nsew\")\n        self.textbox.insert(\"0.0\", \"Paste your transcript here...\")\n        self.textbox.bind(\"<FocusIn>\", self.clear_placeholder)\n        \n        # Bottom controls frame\n        self.controls_frame = ctk.CTkFrame(self, fg_color=\"transparent\")\n        self.controls_frame.grid(row=1, column=0, padx=10, pady=(0, 10), sticky=\"ew\")\n        self.controls_frame.grid_columnconfigure(0, weight=1)\n        \n        # Character count\n        self.char_count = ctk.CTkLabel(self.controls_frame, text=\"Characters: 0\")\n        self.char_count.grid(row=0, column=0, sticky=\"w\")\n        \n        # Clear button\n        self.clear_button = ctk.CTkButton(self.controls_frame, text=\"Clear\", command=self.clear_text)\n        self.clear_button.grid(row=0, column=1, padx=(10, 0))\n        \n        # Setup auto-save timer\n        self.textbox.bind(\"<KeyRelease>\", self.on_text_change)\n        self.last_save_time = 0\n        \n        # Setup keyboard shortcuts\n        self.textbox.bind(\"<Control-a>\", self.select_all)\n    \n    def clear_placeholder(self, event):\n        if self.textbox.get(\"0.0\", \"end-1c\") == \"Paste your transcript here...\":\n            self.textbox.delete(\"0.0\", \"end\")\n    \n    def clear_text(self):\n        self.textbox.delete(\"0.0\", \"end\")\n        self.update_char_count()\n    \n    def on_text_change(self, event):\n        self.update_char_count()\n        current_time = time.time()\n        if current_time - self.last_save_time > 5:  # Auto-save every 5 seconds\n            self.auto_save()\n            self.last_save_time = current_time\n    \n    def update_char_count(self):\n        count = len(self.textbox.get(\"0.0\", \"end-1c\"))\n        self.char_count.configure(text=f\"Characters: {count}\")\n    \n    def auto_save(self):\n        # Implement auto-save functionality\n        # For now just print, but could save to file or local storage\n        print(\"Auto-saving transcript...\")\n    \n    def select_all(self, event):\n        self.textbox.tag_add(\"sel\", \"0.0\", \"end\")\n        return \"break\"  # Prevents default behavior\n```\n\n## Styling Considerations\n- Use system theme detection for light/dark mode compatibility\n- Ensure padding scales appropriately on different screen sizes\n- Consider using a monospaced font for transcript input for better readability\n</info added on 2025-05-05T01:07:26.870Z>",
