        {
          "id": 2,
          "title": "Implement profile listing and selection UI",
          "description": "Create the UI components for displaying, selecting and managing analysis profiles",
          "dependencies": [
            1
          ],
          "details": "Implementation steps:\n1. Create a profile list component that displays existing analysis profiles\n2. Implement a selection mechanism (radio buttons or highlighted selection)\n3. Add a default profile that's pre-selected for new users\n4. Design the profile list item component showing:\n   - Profile name\n   - Brief preview of profile instructions (truncated)\n   - Last used indicator\n5. Implement sorting/filtering options for profiles\n6. Add empty state UI for when no profiles exist\n\nTesting approach:\n- Verify profiles display correctly in the list\n- Test selection mechanism works properly\n- Validate default profile selection\n- Test empty state rendering\n- Ensure profile list is scrollable when many profiles exist\n\n<info added on 2025-05-05T02:13:09.598Z>\nImplementation Plan:\n1. Modify main window grid layout (src/main_app.py) to add a new column for profile management next to the transcript textbox.\n2. Create a ctk.CTkFrame in the new column.\n3. Inside the frame, add a ctk.CTkScrollableFrame.\n4. Fetch profile list (likely using src/profile_repository.py - need to confirm functions).\n5. Populate the scrollable frame with ctk.CTkRadioButtons, one per profile, displaying the name.\n6. Implement logic to store the selected profile ID.\n7. Handle default selection (first profile or a dedicated default) and empty state display.\n\nCode structure:\n```python\n# In src/main_app.py\nself.profile_frame = ctk.CTkFrame(self.main_frame)\nself.profile_frame.grid(row=0, column=1, padx=10, pady=10, sticky=\"nsew\")\n\nself.profile_label = ctk.CTkLabel(self.profile_frame, text=\"Analysis Profiles\")\nself.profile_label.pack(pady=5)\n\nself.profile_scrollable = ctk.CTkScrollableFrame(self.profile_frame)\nself.profile_scrollable.pack(fill=\"both\", expand=True)\n\nself.profile_radio_var = ctk.StringVar(value=\"\")\nself.profile_buttons = {}\n\n# Empty state handling\nself.empty_state_label = ctk.CTkLabel(self.profile_scrollable, \n                                     text=\"No profiles available.\\nCreate your first profile to get started.\")\n\ndef load_profiles(self):\n    profiles = profile_repository.get_all_profiles()\n    \n    # Clear existing buttons\n    for widget in self.profile_scrollable.winfo_children():\n        widget.destroy()\n    \n    if not profiles:\n        self.empty_state_label.pack(pady=20)\n        return\n        \n    # Create radio button for each profile\n    for profile in profiles:\n        radio = ctk.CTkRadioButton(self.profile_scrollable, \n                                  text=profile.name,\n                                  variable=self.profile_radio_var,\n                                  value=str(profile.id),\n                                  command=self.on_profile_selected)\n        radio.pack(anchor=\"w\", pady=5)\n        self.profile_buttons[profile.id] = radio\n        \n    # Select default profile\n    if profiles and self.profile_radio_var.get() == \"\":\n        default_id = self.get_default_profile_id(profiles)\n        self.profile_radio_var.set(str(default_id))\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-05T02:13:09.598Z>",
          "status": "done",
          "parentTaskId": 3
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "title": "Build profile creation and editing form",
          "description": "Implement the UI for creating new profiles and editing existing ones",
          "dependencies": [
            2
          ],
          "details": "Implementation steps:\n1. Create a modal or dedicated view for profile creation/editing\n2. Implement form with the following fields:\n   - Profile name input (with validation)\n   - Instructions text area for detailed analysis guidance\n   - Optional category/tag selection\n3. Add form validation logic:\n   - Required fields validation\n   - Character limits for profile name\n   - Duplicate name prevention\n4. Implement save and cancel buttons with appropriate actions\n5. Add confirmation dialog for canceling with unsaved changes\n\nTesting approach:\n- Test form validation for all fields\n- Verify save functionality correctly creates/updates profiles\n- Test cancel functionality and confirmation dialog\n- Validate that edited profiles update correctly in the profile list\n- Test edge cases like very long profile names or instructions\n\n<info added on 2025-05-05T02:59:36.589Z>\n## Implementation Plan Details\n\n### Component Architecture\n- Use the Model-View-Controller pattern for the profile editor\n- Implement form validation as a separate utility class (`ProfileValidator`) for reusability\n\n### UI Implementation Details\n```python\n# Example implementation for ProfileEditorWindow\nclass ProfileEditorWindow(ctk.CTkToplevel):\n    def __init__(self, master, repository, profile_id=None, on_save_callback=None):\n        super().__init__(master)\n        self.repository = repository\n        self.profile_id = profile_id\n        self.on_save_callback = on_save_callback\n        self.is_dirty = False\n        \n        # Set window properties\n        self.title(\"Edit Profile\" if profile_id else \"Create Profile\")\n        self.geometry(\"500x400\")\n        self.resizable(False, False)\n        \n        # Create form layout with proper padding and grid configuration\n        self._create_widgets()\n        self._load_profile_data()\n        self._bind_events()\n```\n\n### Form Validation Logic\n```python\ndef _validate_form(self):\n    # Get form values\n    name = self.name_entry.get().strip()\n    instructions = self.instructions_text.get(\"1.0\", \"end-1c\").strip()\n    \n    # Validation rules\n    if not name:\n        return False, \"Profile name is required\"\n    \n    if len(name) > 50:\n        return False, \"Profile name must be 50 characters or less\"\n    \n    # Check for duplicate names (excluding current profile)\n    existing = self.repository.get_profile_by_name(name)\n    if existing and (not self.profile_id or existing.id != self.profile_id):\n        return False, \"A profile with this name already exists\"\n        \n    return True, None\n```\n\n### Change Tracking Implementation\n```python\ndef _mark_as_dirty(self, *args):\n    \"\"\"Mark the form as having unsaved changes\"\"\"\n    self.is_dirty = True\n    \ndef _confirm_discard_changes(self):\n    \"\"\"Show confirmation dialog for unsaved changes\"\"\"\n    if not self.is_dirty:\n        return True\n        \n    response = CTkMessagebox(\n        title=\"Unsaved Changes\",\n        message=\"You have unsaved changes. Discard changes?\",\n        icon=\"warning\",\n        option_1=\"Cancel\",\n        option_2=\"Discard\"\n    )\n    return response.get() == \"Discard\"\n```\n\n### Integration with Main App\n```python\n# In MainApp class\ndef _setup_profile_controls(self):\n    # Create button frame\n    btn_frame = ctk.CTkFrame(self.profile_frame)\n    btn_frame.pack(fill=\"x\", padx=10, pady=(5, 10))\n    \n    # Create New Profile button\n    create_btn = ctk.CTkButton(\n        btn_frame, \n        text=\"Create Profile\",\n        command=self._open_profile_editor\n    )\n    create_btn.pack(side=\"left\", padx=5)\n    \n    # Edit Profile button\n    self.edit_btn = ctk.CTkButton(\n        btn_frame, \n        text=\"Edit Profile\",\n        command=self._edit_selected_profile,\n        state=\"disabled\"  # Initially disabled\n    )\n    self.edit_btn.pack(side=\"left\", padx=5)\n```\n\n### Keyboard Shortcuts\n- Add Ctrl+S for saving the profile\n- Add Esc for canceling/closing the editor\n- Implement Tab navigation between form fields\n</info added on 2025-05-05T02:59:36.589Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-05T03:02:22.573Z>\n## Implementation Plan Details\n\n### Form Field Specifications\n- Profile name: Max 50 characters, required, unique\n- Instructions: Multi-line text area with scrollbar, min height 150px\n- Tags/Categories: Implement as CTkCheckboxes in a scrollable frame with common categories\n\n### State Management\n```python\nclass ProfileEditorWindow(ctk.CTkToplevel):\n    def __init__(self, master, repository, profile_id=None, on_save_callback=None):\n        # Initialize state variables\n        self.original_data = {}  # Store original profile data for comparison\n        self.current_tags = set()  # Track selected tags\n        \n    def _track_changes(self):\n        \"\"\"Compare current form state with original data to determine if changes exist\"\"\"\n        current_name = self.name_entry.get().strip()\n        current_instructions = self.instructions_text.get(\"1.0\", \"end-1c\").strip()\n        \n        # Check if any field has changed from original\n        return (current_name != self.original_data.get('name', '') or\n                current_instructions != self.original_data.get('instructions', '') or\n                self.current_tags != set(self.original_data.get('tags', [])))\n```\n\n### Error Handling\n```python\ndef _save_profile(self):\n    try:\n        valid, error_msg = self._validate_form()\n        if not valid:\n            CTkMessagebox(title=\"Validation Error\", message=error_msg, icon=\"cancel\")\n            return False\n            \n        # Create/update profile object\n        profile_data = {\n            'name': self.name_entry.get().strip(),\n            'instructions': self.instructions_text.get(\"1.0\", \"end-1c\").strip(),\n            'tags': list(self.current_tags)\n        }\n        \n        if self.profile_id:\n            profile_data['id'] = self.profile_id\n            \n        success = self.repository.save_profile(profile_data)\n        if not success:\n            CTkMessagebox(title=\"Save Error\", message=\"Failed to save profile\", icon=\"cancel\")\n            return False\n            \n        if self.on_save_callback:\n            self.on_save_callback()\n            \n        self.destroy()\n        return True\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        CTkMessagebox(title=\"Error\", message=f\"An error occurred: {str(e)}\", icon=\"cancel\")\n        return False\n```\n\n### Accessibility Considerations\n- Add tooltips to all form fields using the `CTkToolTip` class\n- Implement keyboard navigation with Tab order\n- Add descriptive labels and placeholders for all fields\n- Ensure proper contrast for text elements\n- Add status messages for screen readers when validation errors occur\n\n### Testing Scenarios\n1. Create profile with minimum required fields\n2. Create profile with all fields populated\n3. Attempt to create profile with duplicate name\n4. Edit profile and save without changes\n5. Edit profile name to match another existing profile\n6. Test very long text in instructions field\n7. Test special characters in profile name\n8. Test cancel with unsaved changes\n9. Test window close (X button) with unsaved changes\n</info added on 2025-05-05T03:02:22.573Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-05T03:14:22.974Z>\n<info added on 2025-05-05T03:05:17.892Z>\n## Tag Selection Implementation Details\n\n### Tag Selection UI Component\n```python\ndef _create_tag_selection(self):\n    # Create frame for tags section\n    tags_frame = ctk.CTkFrame(self.main_frame)\n    tags_frame.pack(fill=\"x\", padx=10, pady=(10, 5))\n    \n    # Add label\n    tags_label = ctk.CTkLabel(tags_frame, text=\"Tags (Optional):\", anchor=\"w\")\n    tags_label.pack(fill=\"x\", padx=5, pady=(5, 0))\n    \n    # Create scrollable frame for tags\n    self.tags_container = ctk.CTkScrollableFrame(tags_frame, height=100)\n    self.tags_container.pack(fill=\"x\", padx=5, pady=5)\n    \n    # Predefined tags\n    self.predefined_tags = [\"Meeting\", \"Interview\", \"Lecture\", \"Presentation\", \n                           \"Brainstorming\", \"Customer Call\", \"Technical\", \"Legal\", \n                           \"Medical\", \"Academic\", \"Personal\", \"Dictation\"]\n    \n    # Tag checkboxes\n    self.tag_vars = {}\n    for i, tag in enumerate(self.predefined_tags):\n        row, col = divmod(i, 3)  # 3 columns of tags\n        var = ctk.BooleanVar(value=False)\n        checkbox = ctk.CTkCheckBox(self.tags_container, text=tag, variable=var,\n                                  command=self._mark_as_dirty)\n        checkbox.grid(row=row, column=col, padx=5, pady=2, sticky=\"w\")\n        self.tag_vars[tag] = var\n```\n\n### Tag Data Handling\n```python\ndef _load_profile_data(self):\n    \"\"\"Load existing profile data into the form\"\"\"\n    if not self.profile_id:\n        self.original_data = {'name': '', 'instructions': '', 'tags': []}\n        return\n        \n    profile = self.repository.get_profile_by_id(self.profile_id)\n    if not profile:\n        return\n        \n    # Load basic profile data\n    self.name_entry.insert(0, profile.name)\n    self.instructions_text.insert(\"1.0\", profile.instructions)\n    \n    # Load tags\n    if hasattr(profile, 'tags') and profile.tags:\n        for tag in profile.tags:\n            if tag in self.tag_vars:\n                self.tag_vars[tag].set(True)\n    \n    # Store original data for change detection\n    self.original_data = {\n        'name': profile.name,\n        'instructions': profile.instructions,\n        'tags': profile.tags if hasattr(profile, 'tags') else []\n    }\n    self.is_dirty = False\n\ndef _get_selected_tags(self):\n    \"\"\"Get list of currently selected tags\"\"\"\n    return [tag for tag, var in self.tag_vars.items() if var.get()]\n\ndef _save_profile(self):\n    # Validation code...\n    \n    # Create profile data dictionary\n    profile_data = {\n        'name': self.name_entry.get().strip(),\n        'instructions': self.instructions_text.get(\"1.0\", \"end-1c\").strip(),\n        'tags': self._get_selected_tags()\n    }\n    \n    # Save profile code...\n```\n\n### Model Updates Required\n```python\n# In src/models/analysis_profile.py\nclass AnalysisProfile:\n    def __init__(self, id=None, name=\"\", instructions=\"\", tags=None):\n        self.id = id\n        self.name = name\n        self.instructions = instructions\n        self.tags = tags or []  # Default to empty list\n        \n    def to_dict(self):\n        return {\n            'id': self.id,\n            'name': self.name,\n            'instructions': self.instructions,\n            'tags': self.tags\n        }\n        \n    @classmethod\n    def from_dict(cls, data):\n        return cls(\n            id=data.get('id'),\n            name=data.get('name', ''),\n            instructions=data.get('instructions', ''),\n            tags=data.get('tags', [])\n        )\n```\n\n### Repository Updates\n```python\n# In src/repositories/profile_repository.py\n# Ensure the save_profile and load_profile methods handle the tags attribute\n\ndef save_profile(self, profile_data):\n    # Existing code...\n    \n    # Make sure to include tags in the serialization\n    if isinstance(profile_data, dict):\n        profile_dict = profile_data\n    else:\n        profile_dict = profile_data.to_dict()\n        \n    # Save to JSON file...\n\ndef load_profiles(self):\n    # When loading profiles, ensure tags are properly deserialized\n    # Existing code...\n    \n    profiles = []\n    for profile_dict in data:\n        # Ensure backward compatibility with profiles that don't have tags\n        if 'tags' not in profile_dict:\n            profile_dict['tags'] = []\n        profiles.append(AnalysisProfile.from_dict(profile_dict))\n```\n\n### Tag Filtering Integration\n```python\n# In src/app.py or main window class\ndef _setup_profile_filter(self):\n    \"\"\"Add tag filtering to the profile list\"\"\"\n    filter_frame = ctk.CTkFrame(self.profile_frame)\n    filter_frame.pack(fill=\"x\", padx=10, pady=(5, 0))\n    \n    filter_label = ctk.CTkLabel(filter_frame, text=\"Filter by tag:\", anchor=\"w\")\n    filter_label.pack(side=\"left\", padx=5)\n    \n    self.tag_filter = ctk.CTkComboBox(\n        filter_frame,\n        values=[\"All\"] + self.predefined_tags,\n        command=self._filter_profiles_by_tag\n    )\n    self.tag_filter.set(\"All\")\n    self.tag_filter.pack(side=\"left\", padx=5)\n    \ndef _filter_profiles_by_tag(self, tag):\n    \"\"\"Filter the profile list by selected tag\"\"\"\n    self.profile_listbox.delete(0, \"end\")\n    \n    profiles = self.profile_repository.get_all_profiles()\n    for profile in profiles:\n        # If \"All\" is selected or profile has the selected tag\n        if tag == \"All\" or (hasattr(profile, 'tags') and tag in profile.tags):\n            self.profile_listbox.insert(\"end\", profile.name)\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-05T03:05:17.892Z>\n</info added on 2025-05-05T03:14:22.974Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-05T04:20:18.623Z>\n## Integration Testing Plan\n\n### Test Cases for Profile Editor Integration\n1. **Creation Flow Test**\n   - Verify \"Create Profile\" button opens a new editor window\n   - Confirm window title shows \"Create Profile\"\n   - Test that saving creates a new profile in the repository\n   - Verify new profile appears in the profile list immediately\n\n2. **Edit Flow Test**\n   - Verify \"Edit Profile\" button is disabled when no profile is selected\n   - Confirm button enables when a profile is selected\n   - Test that editor opens with correct profile data loaded\n   - Verify changes are saved and reflected in the profile list\n\n3. **UI State Management**\n   - Test profile selection in the list properly enables/disables the edit button\n   - Verify multiple rapid clicks don't open multiple editor windows\n   - Test that editor window is modal (blocks interaction with main window)\n   - Verify editor window position is centered relative to main window\n\n### Responsive Design Considerations\n```python\ndef _adjust_for_screen_size(self):\n    \"\"\"Adjust editor size based on screen dimensions\"\"\"\n    # Get screen width and height\n    screen_width = self.winfo_screenwidth()\n    screen_height = self.winfo_screenheight()\n    \n    # Calculate dimensions (responsive to screen size)\n    width = min(600, int(screen_width * 0.6))\n    height = min(500, int(screen_height * 0.7))\n    \n    # Center window\n    x = (screen_width - width) // 2\n    y = (screen_height - height) // 2\n    \n    # Set geometry\n    self.geometry(f\"{width}x{height}+{x}+{y}\")\n```\n\n### Profile Editor Focus Management\n```python\ndef _setup_focus_behavior(self):\n    \"\"\"Configure focus behavior for better UX\"\"\"\n    # Set initial focus to name field\n    self.after(100, lambda: self.name_entry.focus_set())\n    \n    # Prevent closing with Alt+F4 if dirty (show confirmation instead)\n    self.protocol(\"WM_DELETE_WINDOW\", self._on_close_request)\n    \n    # Make window modal to prevent interaction with parent\n    self.grab_set()\n    self.transient(self.master)\n```\n\n### Profile List Refresh Implementation\n```python\n# In MainApp class\ndef _refresh_profile_list(self):\n    \"\"\"Refresh the profile list and maintain selection if possible\"\"\"\n    # Store currently selected profile name if any\n    selected_idx = self.profile_listbox.curselection()\n    selected_name = None\n    if selected_idx:\n        selected_name = self.profile_listbox.get(selected_idx[0])\n    \n    # Clear and reload the list\n    self.profile_listbox.delete(0, tk.END)\n    profiles = self.profile_repository.get_all_profiles()\n    \n    # Sort profiles alphabetically by name\n    profiles.sort(key=lambda p: p.name.lower())\n    \n    # Populate list and try to restore selection\n    new_selected_idx = 0\n    for i, profile in enumerate(profiles):\n        self.profile_listbox.insert(tk.END, profile.name)\n        if profile.name == selected_name:\n            new_selected_idx = i\n    \n    # Restore selection if possible\n    if profiles and selected_name:\n        self.profile_listbox.selection_set(new_selected_idx)\n        self.profile_listbox.see(new_selected_idx)\n```\n\n### Performance Optimization\n- Implement lazy loading of tag checkboxes for improved startup time\n- Use debouncing for change tracking to reduce CPU usage during typing\n- Implement profile caching to avoid unnecessary repository reads\n\n### Accessibility Enhancements\n```python\ndef _setup_accessibility(self):\n    \"\"\"Add accessibility features to the editor\"\"\"\n    # Add screen reader descriptions\n    self.name_entry.configure(takefocus=1)\n    self.instructions_text.configure(takefocus=1)\n    \n    # Add keyboard shortcut labels to buttons\n    self.save_button.configure(text=\"Save (Ctrl+S)\")\n    self.cancel_button.configure(text=\"Cancel (Esc)\")\n    \n    # Add high contrast mode toggle\n    contrast_var = ctk.BooleanVar(value=False)\n    contrast_cb = ctk.CTkCheckBox(\n        self.button_frame, \n        text=\"High contrast\", \n        variable=contrast_var,\n        command=self._toggle_contrast_mode\n    )\n    contrast_cb.pack(side=\"left\", padx=10)\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-05T04:20:18.623Z>",
