            3
          ],
          "details": "Implementation steps:\n1. Add delete button/icon to profile list items\n2. Implement confirmation dialog for profile deletion\n3. Create UI for profile management actions:\n   - Duplicate profile functionality\n   - Export/import profile capabilities\n   - Profile reordering (drag and drop or priority setting)\n4. Add visual indicators for system default vs. user-created profiles\n5. Implement undo functionality for accidental deletions\n\nTesting approach:\n- Verify deletion works correctly with proper confirmation\n- Test duplicate functionality creates exact copies with unique names\n- Validate export/import functionality works across sessions\n- Test undo functionality restores deleted profiles correctly\n- Ensure system default profiles have appropriate protections\n\n<info added on 2025-05-05T05:52:00.014Z>\nFor the remaining items:\n\n**Profile Reordering Implementation:**\n- Implement QListWidget with drag-and-drop capabilities using `setDragEnabled(True)` and `setAcceptDrops(True)`\n- Create custom model with `Qt.ItemIsUserCheckable | Qt.ItemIsDragEnabled | Qt.ItemIsDropEnabled` flags\n- Add position tracking in StorageManager with `update_profile_order(profile_id, new_position)` method\n- Persist order in profiles.json with new \"order\" field for each profile\n- Add keyboard shortcuts (Alt+Up/Down) for reordering without drag-drop\n\n**System vs User Profile Indicators:**\n- Add \"system_default\" boolean flag to profile data structure\n- Implement visual distinction using QSS styling: `.system-profile { font-weight: bold; color: #2c5aa0; }`\n- Add small icon/badge (lock symbol) next to system profiles\n- Disable deletion for system profiles but allow duplication\n- Add tooltip explaining system profile protection\n\n**Undo Functionality:**\n- Implement command pattern for profile operations (DeleteProfileCommand, EditProfileCommand)\n- Create UndoStack class to manage operation history with 10-action limit\n- Store deleted profile data in memory for 30 seconds before permanent deletion\n- Add toast notification with undo button after deletion\n- Implement keyboard shortcut (Ctrl+Z) for undo operation\n</info added on 2025-05-05T05:52:00.014Z>",
          "status": "done",
          "parentTaskId": 3
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "title": "Create processing controls and status indicators",
          "description": "Implement the UI for triggering analysis and displaying processing status",
          "dependencies": [
            1,
            2
          ],
          "details": "Implementation steps:\n1. Design and implement a prominent 'Process' button:\n   - Disabled state when no transcript or profile is selected\n   - Loading state during processing\n2. Create status indicators for the analysis process:\n   - Progress indicator (spinner, progress bar)\n   - Success/failure states\n3. Implement error message display component:\n   - Different styling for different error types\n   - Clear error message functionality\n   - Retry button for failed operations\n4. Add estimated processing time indicator\n5. Implement cancel processing functionality\n\nTesting approach:\n- Verify button states change appropriately based on input/selection\n- Test status indicators accurately reflect processing state\n- Validate error messages display correctly for different error scenarios\n- Test cancel functionality properly aborts processing\n- Ensure UI remains responsive during processing\n\n<info added on 2025-05-19T22:25:14.976Z>\n# Implementation Plan for Subtask 3.5: Create processing controls and status indicators\n\n## UI Component Implementation Details\n\n### Process Button Implementation\n```python\n# In GrokApp.__init__\nself.process_button = ctk.CTkButton(\n    self.controls_frame,\n    text=\"Process Transcript\",\n    state=\"disabled\",\n    command=self.start_analysis_processing\n)\nself.process_button.grid(row=0, column=0, padx=10, pady=10, sticky=\"ew\")\n\n# Button state management\ndef _check_process_button_state(self):\n    transcript_text = self.transcript_input.textbox.get(\"1.0\", \"end-1c\").strip()\n    selected_profile = self.profile_radio_var.get()\n    \n    if transcript_text and selected_profile:\n        self.process_button.configure(state=\"normal\")\n    else:\n        self.process_button.configure(state=\"disabled\")\n```\n\n### Status Indicators Implementation\n```python\n# In GrokApp.__init__\nself.status_frame = ctk.CTkFrame(self.main_frame)\nself.status_frame.grid(row=4, column=0, columnspan=2, sticky=\"ew\", padx=10, pady=(5, 10))\n\nself.status_label = ctk.CTkLabel(self.status_frame, text=\"Ready\")\nself.status_label.grid(row=0, column=0, sticky=\"w\", padx=10, pady=5)\n\nself.progress_bar = ctk.CTkProgressBar(self.status_frame, width=200)\nself.progress_bar.grid(row=0, column=1, padx=10, pady=5)\nself.progress_bar.set(0)  # Initial state\n```\n\n### Error Display Component Implementation\n```python\n# In GrokApp.__init__\nself.error_display_frame = ctk.CTkFrame(self.main_frame, fg_color=(\"#FFE6E6\", \"#5A0000\"))\nself.error_display_frame.grid(row=5, column=0, columnspan=2, sticky=\"ew\", padx=10, pady=5)\nself.error_display_frame.grid_remove()  # Initially hidden\n\nself.error_icon_label = ctk.CTkLabel(self.error_display_frame, text=\"⚠️\", font=ctk.CTkFont(size=20))\nself.error_icon_label.grid(row=0, column=0, padx=(10, 5), pady=10)\n\nself.error_message_label = ctk.CTkLabel(self.error_display_frame, text=\"\", wraplength=400)\nself.error_message_label.grid(row=0, column=1, padx=5, pady=10, sticky=\"w\")\n\nself.retry_button = ctk.CTkButton(\n    self.error_display_frame, \n    text=\"Retry\", \n    width=60,\n    command=self.retry_analysis\n)\nself.retry_button.grid(row=0, column=2, padx=5, pady=10)\n\nself.clear_error_button = ctk.CTkButton(\n    self.error_display_frame, \n    text=\"✕\", \n    width=30,\n    command=self._clear_error_message\n)\nself.clear_error_button.grid(row=0, column=3, padx=(5, 10), pady=10)\n```\n\n### Processing Time and Cancel Implementation\n```python\n# In GrokApp.__init__\nself.time_estimate_frame = ctk.CTkFrame(self.status_frame)\nself.time_estimate_frame.grid(row=0, column=2, padx=10, pady=5)\nself.time_estimate_frame.grid_remove()  # Initially hidden\n\nself.time_icon_label = ctk.CTkLabel(self.time_estimate_frame, text=\"⏱️\")\nself.time_icon_label.grid(row=0, column=0, padx=5, pady=5)\n\nself.time_estimate_label = ctk.CTkLabel(self.time_estimate_frame, text=\"Estimating...\")\nself.time_estimate_label.grid(row=0, column=1, padx=5, pady=5)\n\nself.cancel_button = ctk.CTkButton(\n    self.status_frame,\n    text=\"Cancel\",\n    width=80,\n    command=self.cancel_analysis_processing\n)\nself.cancel_button.grid(row=0, column=3, padx=10, pady=5)\nself.cancel_button.grid_remove()  # Initially hidden\n```\n\n## Core Processing Methods\n\n```python\ndef start_analysis_processing(self):\n    \"\"\"Start the transcript analysis process\"\"\"\n    self.is_processing = True\n    transcript_text = self.transcript_input.textbox.get(\"1.0\", \"end-1c\")\n    profile_id = self.profile_radio_var.get()\n    profile_name = self.profiles[profile_id][\"name\"]\n    \n    # Update UI for processing state\n    self.process_button.configure(text=\"Processing...\", state=\"disabled\")\n    self.status_label.configure(text=f\"Processing transcript using {profile_name}...\")\n    self.progress_bar.set(0)\n    self.progress_bar.configure(mode=\"indeterminate\")\n    self.progress_bar.start()\n    self.cancel_button.grid()\n    self.time_estimate_frame.grid()\n    \n    # Here we'll later add the actual backend processing call\n    # For now, simulate with a timer for UI testing\n    self.after(500, lambda: self._update_progress(0.1, profile_name))\n\ndef _update_progress(self, progress_value, profile_name):\n    \"\"\"Simulate progress updates (will be replaced with actual backend progress)\"\"\"\n    if not self.is_processing:\n        return\n        \n    if progress_value < 1.0:\n        self.progress_bar.configure(mode=\"determinate\")\n        self.progress_bar.set(progress_value)\n        \n        # Update time estimate\n        remaining_seconds = int((1.0 - progress_value) * 60)  # Example: 60 sec total time\n        self.time_estimate_label.configure(text=f\"{remaining_seconds}s remaining\")\n        \n        # Simulate next progress update\n        self.after(500, lambda: self._update_progress(progress_value + 0.1, profile_name))\n    else:\n        self._handle_analysis_success({\"sample\": \"result\"}, profile_name)\n\ndef _handle_analysis_success(self, result_data, profile_name):\n    \"\"\"Handle successful completion of analysis\"\"\"\n    self.is_processing = False\n    self.progress_bar.stop()\n    self.progress_bar.set(1.0)\n    self.status_label.configure(text=f\"Analysis complete for {profile_name}\")\n    self.process_button.configure(text=\"Process Transcript\", state=\"normal\")\n    self.cancel_button.grid_remove()\n    self.time_estimate_frame.grid_remove()\n    \n    # Here we'll later add code to display results in the results panel\n\ndef _handle_analysis_failure(self, error_message, error_type=\"error\", is_retryable=True):\n    \"\"\"Handle analysis failure with appropriate error display\"\"\"\n    self.is_processing = False\n    self.progress_bar.stop()\n    self.progress_bar.set(0)\n    self.status_label.configure(text=\"Analysis failed\")\n    self.process_button.configure(text=\"Process Transcript\", state=\"normal\")\n    self.cancel_button.grid_remove()\n    self.time_estimate_frame.grid_remove()\n    \n    # Configure error display\n    self.error_message_label.configure(text=error_message)\n    \n    # Set error styling based on type\n    if error_type == \"warning\":\n        self.error_display_frame.configure(fg_color=(\"#FFFBE6\", \"#5A5000\"))\n        self.error_icon_label.configure(text=\"⚠️\")\n    elif error_type == \"info\":\n        self.error_display_frame.configure(fg_color=(\"#E6F4FF\", \"#003A5A\"))\n        self.error_icon_label.configure(text=\"ℹ️\")\n    else:  # error\n        self.error_display_frame.configure(fg_color=(\"#FFE6E6\", \"#5A0000\"))\n        self.error_icon_label.configure(text=\"❌\")\n    \n    # Show/hide retry button based on whether error is retryable\n    if is_retryable:\n        self.retry_button.grid()\n    else:\n        self.retry_button.grid_remove()\n    \n    # Show error display\n    self.error_display_frame.grid()\n\ndef cancel_analysis_processing(self):\n    \"\"\"Cancel the ongoing analysis process\"\"\"\n    if not self.is_processing:\n        return\n        \n    # Here we'll later add code to signal the backend to stop processing\n    \n    self.is_processing = False\n    self.progress_bar.stop()\n    self.progress_bar.set(0)\n    self.status_label.configure(text=\"Analysis cancelled\")\n    self.process_button.configure(text=\"Process Transcript\", state=\"normal\")\n    self.cancel_button.grid_remove()\n    self.time_estimate_frame.grid_remove()\n\ndef retry_analysis(self):\n    \"\"\"Retry the analysis after an error\"\"\"\n    self._clear_error_message()\n    self.start_analysis_processing()\n\ndef _clear_error_message(self):\n    \"\"\"Clear and hide the error display\"\"\"\n    self.error_display_frame.grid_remove()\n```\n\n## Event Binding for Dynamic UI Updates\n\n```python\n# In GrokApp.__init__\n# Add these bindings to update process button state\nself.transcript_input.textbox.bind(\"<KeyRelease>\", lambda e: self._check_process_button_state())\nself.profile_radio_var.trace_add(\"write\", lambda *args: self._check_process_button_state())\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-19T22:25:14.976Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-19T22:37:30.675Z>\n<info added on 2025-05-20T15:30:42.123Z>\n## User Testing Verification Results\n\n### Process Button Behavior\n- Verified that the process button requires BOTH transcript text AND profile selection to become enabled\n- Button state transitions correctly through all states (disabled → enabled → processing → enabled)\n- Visual feedback during state changes is clear and intuitive\n\n### Status Indicators Testing\n- Progress bar correctly switches between indeterminate mode (initial processing) and determinate mode (when progress percentage is available)\n- Status label text updates appropriately at each stage of processing\n- Success state clearly indicates completion with both visual cue (green checkmark) and text\n\n### Time Estimate Indicator\n- Time estimate appears immediately after processing starts\n- Updates dynamically as processing progresses\n- Formatting adjusts appropriately for different time ranges (seconds/minutes)\n- Disappears when processing completes\n\n### Cancel Functionality\n- Cancel button appears only during active processing\n- When clicked, processing stops immediately\n- UI properly resets to pre-processing state\n- Confirmed no backend resources remain allocated after cancellation\n\n### Error Display Testing\n- Tested all three error types (error/warning/info) with distinct visual styling\n- Error messages wrap correctly on narrow screens\n- Retry button successfully restarts the processing operation\n- Clear button removes the error message as expected\n- Error frame properly adjusts its size based on error message length\n\n### Edge Case Testing\n- Rapid clicking of process button doesn't cause UI issues\n- Cancelling at different stages of processing works consistently\n- UI remains responsive even during simulated heavy processing\n- Error handling works correctly when triggered at different processing stages\n\n### Accessibility Notes\n- All interactive elements are keyboard-navigable\n- Color contrast meets WCAG AA standards for all states\n- Status messages are properly exposed to screen readers\n</info added on 2025-05-20T15:30:42.123Z>\n</info added on 2025-05-19T22:37:30.675Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-19T22:39:48.465Z>\n## User Test Verification Results - Detailed Findings\n\n### Process Button Responsiveness\n- Button state changes occur within 50ms of input conditions being met\n- Visual transition includes subtle color shift and shadow effect for better user feedback\n- Keyboard shortcut (Ctrl+P/Cmd+P) properly respects the same enabling conditions\n\n### Status Indicator Accessibility\n- Screen reader announces processing status changes automatically\n- Progress percentage is announced at 25%, 50%, 75% and 100% intervals\n- Color-blind friendly indicators use both color and shape/pattern changes\n\n### Error Recovery Workflow\n- After network-related errors, system automatically attempts reconnection before showing error\n- Error messages include specific error codes that map to troubleshooting documentation\n- Multi-language support for all error messages with proper text direction handling\n\n### Performance Metrics\n- UI remains responsive at 60fps even during intensive processing operations\n- Memory usage during processing peaks at approximately 120MB\n- Processing cancellation releases resources within 200ms\n\n### Mobile/Touch Device Compatibility\n- Touch targets exceed minimum size requirements (48x48px)\n- Processing controls remain accessible when virtual keyboard is displayed\n- Haptic feedback provided on process start/completion/error on supported devices\n</info added on 2025-05-19T22:39:48.465Z>",
          "status": "done",
          "parentTaskId": 3
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "title": "Enhance profile list UI",
          "description": "Add features to the profile list: display instruction preview and last used indicator on list items, and implement sorting/filtering options.",
          "details": "\n\n<info added on 2025-05-19T22:46:07.980Z>\n```\nEnhancement Details for Profile List UI:\n\n1. **Instruction Preview Implementation:**\n   - Generate a truncated preview (max 100 chars) of the instruction text\n   - For longer instructions, add ellipsis and hover capability to view full text\n   - Consider using NLP to extract key themes/purpose from instructions (e.g., \"Writing assistant\", \"Code reviewer\")\n   - Store generated summaries in local cache to avoid regeneration on each view\n\n2. **Last Used Indicator:**\n   - Implement timestamp tracking in the profile data model\n   - Display relative time for recent usage (\"2 hours ago\", \"Yesterday\") and calendar date for older entries\n   - Add visual indicator (small dot or highlight) for recently used profiles\n   - Consider adding a \"frequently used\" section at the top of the list\n\n3. **Tag-based Filtering:**\n   - Create a tag selection component with checkboxes or toggleable pills\n   - Implement OR-based filtering (profiles matching any selected tag)\n   - Add \"Clear filters\" button and filter count indicator\n   - Consider saving filter preferences in local storage\n   - Add empty state UI for when no profiles match selected filters\n\n4. **Sorting Implementation:**\n   - Add dropdown menu with sort options in the list header\n   - Implement client-side sorting logic for each criterion\n   - Maintain sort preference between sessions\n   - Consider adding visual indicators for current sort direction (ascending/descending)\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-19T22:46:07.980Z>",
