    {
      "id": 4,
      "title": "Develop core analysis logic for single profile",
      "description": "Implement the backend logic to process a transcript using a single selected Analysis Profile via the Xai Grok API.",
      "status": "done",
      "dependencies": [
        1,
        2,
        3
      ],
      "priority": "high",
      "details": "1. Create an AnalysisJob model to track processing state\n2. Implement function to format transcript and profile instructions for API call\n3. Develop core analysis method that uses XaiGrokConnector to send request\n4. Add logic to parse and validate the JSON response\n5. Create AnalysisResult model to store output\n6. Implement error handling for failed analyses\n7. Add logging for analysis steps\n8. Create utility functions for handling common analysis tasks",
      "testStrategy": "Test with sample transcripts and profiles, verify correct API call formatting, validate response handling, check error scenarios, and ensure proper result storage.",
      "subtasks": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "title": "Create AnalysisJob and AnalysisResult data models",
          "description": "Design and implement the data models needed to track analysis state and store results",
          "dependencies": [],
          "details": "1. Create an AnalysisJob model with fields for: id, status (enum: pending, processing, completed, failed), created_at, updated_at, transcript_id (foreign key), profile_id (foreign key), error_message (nullable)\n2. Create an AnalysisResult model with fields for: id, analysis_job_id (foreign key), raw_response (JSON field), parsed_data (JSON field), created_at\n3. Implement model relationships between AnalysisJob, AnalysisResult, Transcript, and Profile\n4. Add appropriate indexes for query performance\n5. Write database migrations\n6. Create basic model tests to verify relationships and constraints\n7. Add model validation rules for required fields\n\n<info added on 2025-05-20T01:06:06.760Z>\nHere's additional implementation information for the data models:\n\n```python\n# Example implementation for AnalysisJob model\nclass AnalysisJob:\n    def __init__(self, id=None, status=\"pending\", transcript_id=None, profile_id=None, \n                 temporary_instructions=None, error_message=None, created_at=None, updated_at=None):\n        self.id = id\n        self.status = status\n        self.transcript_id = transcript_id\n        self.profile_id = profile_id\n        self.temporary_instructions = temporary_instructions\n        self.error_message = error_message\n        self.created_at = created_at or datetime.datetime.now()\n        self.updated_at = updated_at or datetime.datetime.now()\n        \n    def to_dict(self):\n        return {\n            \"id\": self.id,\n            \"status\": self.status,\n            \"transcript_id\": self.transcript_id,\n            \"profile_id\": self.profile_id,\n            \"temporary_instructions\": self.temporary_instructions,\n            \"error_message\": self.error_message,\n            \"created_at\": self.created_at.isoformat() if self.created_at else None,\n            \"updated_at\": self.updated_at.isoformat() if self.updated_at else None\n        }\n```\n\nFor database schema, consider these SQL statements for migrations:\n\n```sql\n-- Create AnalysisJob table\nCREATE TABLE analysis_jobs (\n    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    status TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed')),\n    transcript_id INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    profile_id INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    temporary_instructions TEXT,\n    error_message TEXT,\n    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,\n    updated_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,\n    FOREIGN KEY (transcript_id) REFERENCES transcripts(id),\n    FOREIGN KEY (profile_id) REFERENCES analysis_profiles(id)\n);\n\n-- Create indexes for performance\nCREATE INDEX idx_analysis_jobs_transcript_id ON analysis_jobs(transcript_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_analysis_jobs_profile_id ON analysis_jobs(profile_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_analysis_jobs_status ON analysis_jobs(status);\n```\n\nFor validation, implement methods like:\n```python\ndef validate(self):\n    \"\"\"Validate model data before saving\"\"\"\n    errors = []\n    if not self.transcript_id:\n        errors.append(\"Transcript ID is required\")\n    if not self.profile_id:\n        errors.append(\"Profile ID is required\")\n    if self.status not in [\"pending\", \"processing\", \"completed\", \"failed\"]:\n        errors.append(\"Invalid status value\")\n    return errors\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-20T01:06:06.760Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-20T01:07:32.755Z>\n<info added on 2025-05-20T01:06:06.760Z>\nHere's additional implementation information for the validation and testing:\n\n```python\n# Enhanced validation in AnalysisJob model\nclass JobStatus(enum.Enum):\n    PENDING = \"pending\"\n    PROCESSING = \"processing\"\n    COMPLETED = \"completed\"\n    FAILED = \"failed\"\n\nclass AnalysisJob:\n    def __init__(self, id=None, status=JobStatus.PENDING, transcript_id=None, profile_id=None, \n                 temporary_instructions=None, error_message=None, created_at=None, updated_at=None):\n        # Validation logic\n        if not transcript_id:\n            raise ValueError(\"transcript_id is required\")\n        \n        if not isinstance(status, JobStatus) and status not in [s.value for s in JobStatus]:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Invalid status: {status}\")\n            \n        if not profile_id and not temporary_instructions:\n            raise ValueError(\"Either profile_id or temporary_instructions must be provided\")\n            \n        # Convert string status to enum if needed\n        if isinstance(status, str):\n            status = JobStatus(status)\n            \n        # Initialize fields\n        self.id = id\n        self.status = status\n        self.transcript_id = transcript_id\n        self.profile_id = profile_id\n        self.temporary_instructions = temporary_instructions\n        self.error_message = error_message\n        self.created_at = created_at or datetime.datetime.now()\n        self.updated_at = updated_at or datetime.datetime.now()\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def from_dict(cls, data):\n        \"\"\"Create an AnalysisJob instance from a dictionary\"\"\"\n        # Handle status conversion from string to enum\n        status = data.get(\"status\")\n        if status and isinstance(status, str):\n            try:\n                status = JobStatus(status)\n            except ValueError:\n                raise ValueError(f\"Invalid status value: {status}\")\n        \n        return cls(\n            id=data.get(\"id\"),\n            status=status or JobStatus.PENDING,\n            transcript_id=data.get(\"transcript_id\"),\n            profile_id=data.get(\"profile_id\"),\n            temporary_instructions=data.get(\"temporary_instructions\"),\n            error_message=data.get(\"error_message\"),\n            created_at=data.get(\"created_at\"),\n            updated_at=data.get(\"updated_at\")\n        )\n```\n\nExample unit test implementation:\n\n```python\n# tests/test_analysis_job_result.py\nimport unittest\nimport datetime\nfrom src.models.analysis_job_result import AnalysisJob, AnalysisResult, JobStatus\n\nclass TestAnalysisJob(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_init_with_valid_data(self):\n        \"\"\"Test creating an AnalysisJob with valid data\"\"\"\n        job = AnalysisJob(\n            transcript_id=1,\n            profile_id=2\n        )\n        self.assertEqual(job.transcript_id, 1)\n        self.assertEqual(job.profile_id, 2)\n        self.assertEqual(job.status, JobStatus.PENDING)\n        self.assertIsNone(job.error_message)\n        \n    def test_init_with_invalid_status(self):\n        \"\"\"Test validation of status field\"\"\"\n        with self.assertRaises(ValueError):\n            AnalysisJob(transcript_id=1, profile_id=2, status=\"invalid_status\")\n            \n    def test_init_without_transcript_id(self):\n        \"\"\"Test validation requiring transcript_id\"\"\"\n        with self.assertRaises(ValueError):\n            AnalysisJob(profile_id=2)\n            \n    def test_init_without_profile_or_instructions(self):\n        \"\"\"Test validation requiring either profile_id or temporary_instructions\"\"\"\n        with self.assertRaises(ValueError):\n            AnalysisJob(transcript_id=1)\n            \n    def test_to_dict(self):\n        \"\"\"Test conversion to dictionary\"\"\"\n        now = datetime.datetime.now()\n        job = AnalysisJob(\n            id=1,\n            transcript_id=2,\n            profile_id=3,\n            status=JobStatus.PROCESSING,\n            created_at=now,\n            updated_at=now\n        )\n        job_dict = job.to_dict()\n        self.assertEqual(job_dict[\"id\"], 1)\n        self.assertEqual(job_dict[\"transcript_id\"], 2)\n        self.assertEqual(job_dict[\"profile_id\"], 3)\n        self.assertEqual(job_dict[\"status\"], \"processing\")\n        \n    def test_from_dict(self):\n        \"\"\"Test creating object from dictionary\"\"\"\n        job_dict = {\n            \"id\": 1,\n            \"transcript_id\": 2,\n            \"profile_id\": 3,\n            \"status\": \"completed\"\n        }\n        job = AnalysisJob.from_dict(job_dict)\n        self.assertEqual(job.id, 1)\n        self.assertEqual(job.transcript_id, 2)\n        self.assertEqual(job.profile_id, 3)\n        self.assertEqual(job.status, JobStatus.COMPLETED)\n        \n    def test_from_dict_with_invalid_status(self):\n        \"\"\"Test validation in from_dict method\"\"\"\n        job_dict = {\n            \"transcript_id\": 2,\n            \"profile_id\": 3,\n            \"status\": \"invalid\"\n        }\n        with self.assertRaises(ValueError):\n            AnalysisJob.from_dict(job_dict)\n```\n\nFor the AnalysisResult model, similar validation patterns should be implemented:\n\n```python\nclass AnalysisResult:\n    def __init__(self, id=None, analysis_job_id=None, raw_response=None, \n                 parsed_data=None, created_at=None):\n        # Validation\n        if not analysis_job_id:\n            raise ValueError(\"analysis_job_id is required\")\n        if not raw_response:\n            raise ValueError(\"raw_response is required\")\n            \n        # Initialize fields\n        self.id = id\n        self.analysis_job_id = analysis_job_id\n        self.raw_response = raw_response\n        self.parsed_data = parsed_data\n        self.created_at = created_at or datetime.datetime.now()\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-20T01:06:06.760Z>\n</info added on 2025-05-20T01:07:32.755Z>",
          "status": "done",
          "parentTaskId": 4
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "title": "Implement XaiGrokConnector integration",
          "description": "Create a service class to handle communication with the Xai Grok API",
          "dependencies": [],
          "details": "1. Create XaiGrokConnector class with configuration for API endpoints and authentication\n2. Implement method to format and validate API request payload\n3. Create send_analysis_request method that handles HTTP communication with Xai Grok API\n4. Add timeout handling and retry logic for API calls\n5. Implement proper error handling for network issues, authentication failures, and API errors\n6. Create mock responses for testing\n7. Write unit tests using mocked API responses\n8. Add detailed logging for API interactions\n\n<info added on 2025-05-20T01:25:44.932Z>\n# Implementation Details for XaiGrokConnector\n\n## Class Structure and Configuration\n\n```python\n# src/connectors/xai_grok_connector.py\nimport logging\nimport time\nimport requests\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, Optional\nfrom .base_connector import BaseLLMConnector\nfrom config import settings\n\nclass XaiGrokConnector(BaseLLMConnector):\n    \"\"\"\n    Connector for the Xai Grok API that handles communication, formatting, and error handling.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self, \n        api_key: str = settings.XAI_API_KEY,\n        api_endpoint: str = settings.XAI_API_ENDPOINT,\n        default_model: str = settings.DEFAULT_GROK_MODEL,\n        timeout: int = settings.REQUEST_TIMEOUT_SECONDS\n    ):\n        self.api_key = api_key\n        self.api_endpoint = api_endpoint\n        self.default_model = default_model\n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n        \n        # Initialize session for connection pooling\n        self.session = requests.Session()\n        self.session.headers.update({\n            \"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {self.api_key}\",\n            \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n        })\n```\n\n## Request Payload Formatting\n\n```python\ndef _prepare_request_payload(\n    self, \n    transcript_text: str, \n    profile_instructions: str, \n    model: Optional[str] = None, \n    **kwargs\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Format the input data into the structure expected by the Xai Grok API.\n    \n    Args:\n        transcript_text: The transcript to analyze\n        profile_instructions: Instructions for the analysis\n        model: The model to use (defaults to self.default_model)\n        **kwargs: Additional parameters to include in the request\n        \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing the formatted request payload\n    \"\"\"\n    if not transcript_text:\n        raise ValueError(\"Transcript text cannot be empty\")\n    \n    # Create message structure\n    messages = [\n        {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": profile_instructions},\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": transcript_text}\n    ]\n    \n    # Build the payload\n    payload = {\n        \"model\": model or self.default_model,\n        \"messages\": messages,\n        # Default parameters\n        \"temperature\": 0.7,\n        \"max_tokens\": 1024,\n    }\n    \n    # Override defaults with any provided kwargs\n    payload.update(kwargs)\n    \n    self._log_request(\"POST\", self.api_endpoint, payload)\n    return payload\n```\n\n## API Communication with Retry Logic\n\n```python\ndef send_analysis_request(\n    self, \n    transcript_text: str, \n    profile_instructions: str, \n    model: Optional[str] = None, \n    retries: int = settings.MAX_RETRIES, \n    **kwargs\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Send a request to the Xai Grok API with retry logic and error handling.\n    \n    Args:\n        transcript_text: The transcript to analyze\n        profile_instructions: Instructions for the analysis\n        model: The model to use (defaults to self.default_model)\n        retries: Number of retry attempts for transient errors\n        **kwargs: Additional parameters to include in the request\n        \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing the API response\n        \n    Raises:\n        AuthenticationError: If API key is invalid\n        RateLimitError: If rate limits are exceeded\n        APIError: For other API errors\n        ConnectionError: For network issues\n    \"\"\"\n    payload = self._prepare_request_payload(\n        transcript_text, profile_instructions, model, **kwargs\n    )\n    \n    # Retry logic with exponential backoff\n    for attempt in range(retries + 1):\n        try:\n            response = self.session.post(\n                self.api_endpoint,\n                json=payload,\n                timeout=self.timeout\n            )\n            \n            # Handle successful response\n            if response.status_code == 200:\n                result = response.json()\n                self._log_response(response)\n                return result\n                \n            # Handle rate limiting with retry\n            if response.status_code == 429:\n                if attempt < retries:\n                    wait_time = 2 ** attempt + 1  # Exponential backoff\n                    self.logger.warning(\n                        f\"Rate limit exceeded. Retrying in {wait_time}s. \"\n                        f\"Attempt {attempt + 1}/{retries}\"\n                    )\n                    time.sleep(wait_time)\n                    continue\n                else:\n                    return self._handle_api_error(response)\n            \n            # Handle other errors\n            return self._handle_api_error(response)\n            \n        except requests.exceptions.Timeout:\n            self.logger.error(f\"Request timed out. Attempt {attempt + 1}/{retries}\")\n            if attempt >= retries:\n                raise ConnectionError(\"Request timed out after multiple attempts\")\n        \n        except requests.exceptions.ConnectionError as e:\n            self.logger.error(f\"Connection error: {str(e)}. Attempt {attempt + 1}/{retries}\")\n            if attempt >= retries:\n                raise ConnectionError(f\"Failed to connect to API: {str(e)}\")\n        \n        # Exponential backoff before retry\n        if attempt < retries:\n            time.sleep(2 ** attempt)\n```\n\n## Error Handling and Logging\n\n```python\ndef _handle_api_error(self, response) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Handle API error responses and raise appropriate exceptions\"\"\"\n    error_msg = f\"API Error {response.status_code}: \"\n    \n    try:\n        error_data = response.json()\n        error_msg += error_data.get('error', {}).get('message', 'Unknown error')\n    except ValueError:\n        error_msg += response.text or \"No error details available\"\n    \n    self.logger.error(error_msg)\n    \n    if response.status_code == 401:\n        raise AuthenticationError(\"Invalid API key or authentication failure\")\n    elif response.status_code == 403:\n        raise AuthorizationError(\"Not authorized to access this resource\")\n    elif response.status_code == 429:\n        raise RateLimitError(\"Rate limit exceeded\")\n    elif 400 <= response.status_code < 500:\n        raise InvalidRequestError(error_msg)\n    else:\n        raise APIError(error_msg)\n\ndef _log_request(self, method, url, payload):\n    \"\"\"Log API request details (redacting sensitive information)\"\"\"\n    # Create a copy to avoid modifying the original payload\n    safe_payload = payload.copy() if payload else {}\n    \n    # Redact sensitive information if present\n    if 'api_key' in safe_payload:\n        safe_payload['api_key'] = '***REDACTED***'\n    \n    self.logger.debug(\n        f\"API Request: {method} {url}\\n\"\n        f\"Payload: {safe_payload}\"\n    )\n\ndef _log_response(self, response):\n    \"\"\"Log API response details\"\"\"\n    self.logger.debug(\n        f\"API Response: {response.status_code}\\n\"\n        f\"Headers: {dict(response.headers)}\\n\"\n        f\"Content: {response.text[:500]}{'...' if len(response.text) > 500 else ''}\"\n    )\n```\n\n## Custom Exception Classes\n\n```python\n# src/connectors/exceptions.py\nclass APIError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for API errors\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass AuthenticationError(APIError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when authentication fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass AuthorizationError(APIError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when the request is not authorized\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass InvalidRequestError(APIError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when the request is invalid\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass RateLimitError(APIError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when rate limits are exceeded\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n## Mock Response for Testing\n\n```python\n# tests/mocks/xai_grok_responses.py\nMOCK_SUCCESS_RESPONSE = {\n    \"id\": \"chatcmpl-123456789\",\n    \"object\": \"chat.completion\",\n    \"created\": 1677858242,\n    \"model\": \"grok-1\",\n    \"choices\": [\n        {\n            \"message\": {\n                \"role\": \"assistant\",\n                \"content\": \"This is a mock response from the Xai Grok API. The analysis shows that the transcript contains discussion about project planning and task allocation.\"\n            },\n            \"finish_reason\": \"stop\",\n            \"index\": 0\n        }\n    ],\n    \"usage\": {\n        \"prompt_tokens\": 56,\n        \"completion_tokens\": 31,\n        \"total_tokens\": 87\n    }\n}\n\nMOCK_ERROR_RESPONSES = {\n    400: {\n        \"error\": {\n            \"message\": \"Invalid request: The 'messages' field is required\",\n            \"type\": \"invalid_request_error\",\n            \"code\": \"invalid_messages\"\n        }\n    },\n    401: {\n        \"error\": {\n            \"message\": \"Invalid API key\",\n            \"type\": \"authentication_error\",\n            \"code\": \"invalid_api_key\"\n        }\n    },\n    429: {\n        \"error\": {\n            \"message\": \"Rate limit exceeded. Please try again later.\",\n            \"type\": \"rate_limit_error\",\n            \"code\": \"rate_limit_exceeded\"\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-20T01:25:44.932Z>",
