        {
          "id": 3,
          "title": "Develop core analysis processing function",
          "description": "Implement the main function that processes a transcript using a profile via the API",
          "dependencies": [
            1,
            2
          ],
          "details": "1. Create process_transcript_with_profile function that accepts transcript_id and profile_id parameters\n2. Implement logic to create a new AnalysisJob record with pending status\n3. Add function to format transcript text and profile instructions into API-compatible format\n4. Use XaiGrokConnector to send the formatted request to the API\n5. Update AnalysisJob status during processing steps\n6. Implement transaction handling to ensure data consistency\n7. Add comprehensive logging throughout the process\n8. Write unit tests with mocked dependencies\n9. Create integration test covering the full analysis flow\n\n<info added on 2025-05-20T03:29:21.237Z>\n# Implementation Details for `process_transcript_with_profile` Function\n\n## Architecture and Design\n\nThe function will follow a state machine pattern, where the `AnalysisJob` transitions through different states (PENDING → PROCESSING → COMPLETED/FAILED) with appropriate error handling at each step.\n\n## XaiGrokConnector Integration\n\n```python\nclass XaiGrokConnector:\n    def __init__(self, api_key=None, base_url=None):\n        self.api_key = api_key or os.environ.get(\"XAI_GROK_API_KEY\")\n        self.base_url = base_url or os.environ.get(\"XAI_GROK_API_URL\", \"https://api.xaigrok.com/v1\")\n        self.session = requests.Session()\n        self.session.headers.update({\n            \"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {self.api_key}\",\n            \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n        })\n    \n    def send_analysis_request(self, transcript_text, profile_instructions):\n        \"\"\"Format and send analysis request to XaiGrok API\"\"\"\n        payload = {\n            \"model\": \"grok-analysis-v1\",\n            \"messages\": [\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": profile_instructions},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": transcript_text}\n            ],\n            \"temperature\": 0.2,  # Lower temperature for more consistent analysis\n            \"max_tokens\": 2048\n        }\n        \n        response = self.session.post(f\"{self.base_url}/chat/completions\", json=payload)\n        if response.status_code != 200:\n            raise APIError(f\"API request failed with status {response.status_code}: {response.text}\")\n        \n        return response.json()\n```\n\n## Error Handling Strategy\n\nImplement a custom exception hierarchy:\n\n```python\nclass AnalysisProcessingError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for analysis processing errors\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass TranscriptNotFoundError(AnalysisProcessingError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when transcript cannot be found\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass ProfileNotFoundError(AnalysisProcessingError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when profile cannot be found\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass APIError(AnalysisProcessingError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when API communication fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n## Transaction Management\n\n```python\ndef process_transcript_with_profile(...):\n    # ... existing implementation ...\n    \n    # Transaction handling example\n    try:\n        with db_session.begin():\n            # Create initial job record\n            job = AnalysisJob(...)\n            db_session.add(job)\n            db_session.flush()  # Get the job ID\n            \n            # Fetch required data\n            transcript = db_session.query(Transcript).get(transcript_id)\n            if not transcript:\n                raise TranscriptNotFoundError(f\"Transcript {transcript_id} not found\")\n            \n            # Update job status to PROCESSING\n            job.status = JobStatus.PROCESSING\n            \n            # API call happens outside transaction boundary\n        \n        # API interaction (outside transaction)\n        api_response = connector.send_analysis_request(...)\n        \n        # Store results in a new transaction\n        with db_session.begin():\n            result = AnalysisResult(\n                job_id=job.id,\n                raw_response=json.dumps(api_response),\n                processed_data=parse_analysis_response(api_response)\n            )\n            db_session.add(result)\n            job.status = JobStatus.COMPLETED\n            \n    except Exception as e:\n        # Error handling in a separate transaction\n        with db_session.begin():\n            job.status = JobStatus.FAILED\n            job.error_message = str(e)\n    \n    return job\n```\n\n## Logging Implementation\n\n```python\ndef process_transcript_with_profile(...):\n    logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n    request_id = str(uuid.uuid4())  # Generate unique ID for request tracing\n    \n    logger.info(f\"[{request_id}] Starting analysis process for transcript {transcript_id} with profile {profile_id}\")\n    \n    # ... implementation with structured logging ...\n    \n    try:\n        # ... existing code ...\n        logger.info(f\"[{request_id}] Created analysis job with ID {job.id}\")\n        \n        # ... more implementation ...\n        \n        logger.info(f\"[{request_id}] API request successful, processing response\")\n        \n    except TranscriptNotFoundError as e:\n        logger.error(f\"[{request_id}] Transcript not found: {str(e)}\")\n        # ... error handling ...\n    \n    # ... more implementation ...\n    \n    logger.info(f\"[{request_id}] Analysis completed with status {job.status}\")\n```\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\nFor large transcripts, implement chunking logic:\n\n```python\ndef _chunk_transcript(text, max_chunk_size=8000):\n    \"\"\"Split large transcripts into manageable chunks\"\"\"\n    # Simple sentence-based chunking\n    sentences = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?])\\s+', text)\n    chunks = []\n    current_chunk = \"\"\n    \n    for sentence in sentences:\n        if len(current_chunk) + len(sentence) <= max_chunk_size:\n            current_chunk += sentence + \" \"\n        else:\n            chunks.append(current_chunk.strip())\n            current_chunk = sentence + \" \"\n    \n    if current_chunk:\n        chunks.append(current_chunk.strip())\n    \n    return chunks\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-20T03:29:21.237Z>\n\n<info added on 2025-05-20T03:42:33.227Z>\n<info added on 2025-05-21T14:22:45.123Z>\n# Model Consistency Updates for `process_transcript_with_profile`\n\n## Type Consistency for `profile_id`\n\n```python\ndef process_transcript_with_profile(transcript_id: int, profile_id: int, **kwargs) -> AnalysisJob:\n    \"\"\"\n    Process a transcript using a specific analysis profile.\n    \n    Args:\n        transcript_id: Integer ID of the transcript to analyze\n        profile_id: Integer ID of the analysis profile to use\n        **kwargs: Additional parameters for processing configuration\n        \n    Returns:\n        AnalysisJob: The created job object with processing status\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n## Updated Model Import and Fallback\n\n```python\ntry:\n    from src.models.analysis_profile import AnalysisProfile\nexcept ImportError:\n    # For testing/development without full model implementation\n    class AnalysisProfile:\n        def __init__(self, id: Optional[int] = None, name: str = \"\", \n                     schema_definition: str = \"\", description: str = \"\"):\n            self.id = id\n            self.name = name\n            self.schema_definition = schema_definition\n            self.description = description\n```\n\n## Mock Implementation for Testing\n\n```python\ndef get_profile_by_id(profile_id: int) -> Optional[AnalysisProfile]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Mock implementation to retrieve an analysis profile by ID.\n    Will be replaced with actual database query.\n    \n    Args:\n        profile_id: Integer ID of the profile to retrieve\n        \n    Returns:\n        AnalysisProfile or None if not found\n    \"\"\"\n    # Mock profile for testing\n    if profile_id == 1:\n        return AnalysisProfile(\n            id=1,\n            name=\"Standard Analysis\",\n            schema_definition=\"\"\"\n            {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\n                    \"sentiment\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"positive\", \"neutral\", \"negative\"]},\n                    \"key_points\": {\"type\": \"array\", \"items\": {\"type\": \"string\"}}\n                }\n            }\n            \"\"\",\n            description=\"Standard transcript analysis profile\"\n        )\n    return None\n```\n\n## Job Creation with Consistent Types\n\n```python\n# Create the analysis job with proper typing\njob = AnalysisJob(\n    transcript_id=transcript_id,\n    profile_id=profile_id,  # Ensuring this is an integer\n    status=JobStatus.PENDING,\n    created_at=datetime.now(),\n    updated_at=datetime.now()\n)\n```\n\n## Database Interaction with Type Safety\n\n```python\ndef _get_transcript_by_id(transcript_id: int) -> Optional[Transcript]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Retrieve transcript by ID with proper type handling.\n    \n    Args:\n        transcript_id: Integer ID of the transcript\n        \n    Returns:\n        Transcript object or None if not found\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        # When using SQLAlchemy\n        return db_session.query(Transcript).filter(Transcript.id == transcript_id).first()\n    except Exception as e:\n        logger.error(f\"Database error retrieving transcript {transcript_id}: {str(e)}\")\n        return None\n```\n</info added on 2025-05-21T14:22:45.123Z>\n</info added on 2025-05-20T03:42:33.227Z>",
